The '''Netcare System''' is part of the ''Digital India'' campaign introduced by [[India]]n [[Prime Minister of India|Prime Minister]] [[Narendra Modi]]. The program is designed to allow access to modern [[software]] technology by those in rural areas, villages, and other remote parts of India. A major focus is enabling poor and rural students to use the [[Internet]] and related [[computer technology|computer tech]] and [[information technology]].
