'''Racial transformation''' is the process by which a demographic region (e.g., a country, neighborhood, or a school) changes in racial composition.<ref>{{cite book|last=Orfield|first=G. and Lee, C.|title=Racial Transformation and the Changing Nature of Segregation.|date=2006|publisher=Harvard University|location=Cambridge, MA|url=http://files.eric.ed.gov/fulltext/ED500822.pdf}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Wilson|first=Bobby, M.|title=America's Johannesburg:  Industrialization and Racial Transformation in Birmingham.|date=2000|publisher=Rowman and Littlefield Publishers, Inc.|url=https://books.google.com/?id=c1KZxDcASssC&pg=PR9&dq=Racial+transformation#v=onepage&q=Racial%20transformation&f=false|isbn=9780847694815}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=Durrheim|first=Kevin|title=White Opposition to Racial Transformation. Is it Racism?|journal=South African Journal of Psychology|date=2009|volume=38|issue=4|pages=615–632|doi=10.1177/008124630303300407|url=http://sap.sagepub.com/content/33/4/241.short|accessdate=12 February 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=Durrheim|first=Kevin|author2=John Dixon |author3=Colin Tredoux |author4=Liberty Eaton |author5=Michael Quayle |author6=Beverley Clack |title=Predicting support for racial transformation policies: Intergroup threat, racial prejudice, sense of group entitlement and strength of identification|journal=European Journal of Social Psychology|date=2011|volume=42|issue=1|pages=23–41|doi=10.1002/ejsp.723}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Rosen|first=Louis|title=The South Side: The Racial Transformation of an American Neighborhood|date=1998|publisher=Ivan R. Dee, Publisher|location=Chicago, IL, USA|isbn=978-1566632744|url=https://books.google.com/?id=G8kI2RBBH8cC&pg=PP2&dq=Racial+transformation#v=onepage&q=Racial%20transformation&f=false}}</ref>

